4 Before you Run Remove The Linux Desktop Environment With sudo apt remove sudo dnf remove sudo pacman -Rns 
5 run sudo nano /etc/os-release
6 Change To PRETTY_NAME=Nano OS NAME=Nano OS And ID=nanoos And HOME_URL=
7 Ctrl X Y Enter
8 sudo update-initramfs -u sudo update-grub
9 Go To sudo nano /etc/issue
  Then Change Ubuntu Debian etc To After You Login Run python3 nano_os.py
  Also go to sudo nano /etc/issue.net then do the same thing as Go To sudo nano /etc/issue Change Ubuntu Debian etc To After You Login Run python3 nano_os.py
  If Theres No Sudo Go To sudo nano /etc/issue
  Then Change Ubuntu Debian etc To After You Login Run su - then run python3 nano_os.py
  Also go to sudo nano /etc/issue.net then do the same thing as Go To sudo nano /etc/issue Change Ubuntu Debian etc To After You Login Run su - then python3 nano_os.py
10 go to sudo nano /etc/default/grub
  change "" quiet splash etc to quiet Example GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet"
  Change echo debian ubuntu etc to Nano OS
  Then sudo nano /etc/grub.d/10_linux
  Then change OS=GNU/Linux To OS= And Also OS="${GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR} GNU/Linux" To OS="${GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR}"
  sudo update-grub

11 Run With python3 nano_os.py

